<definitions xmlns="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:flowable="http://flowable.org/bpmn" xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI" xmlns:omgdc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC" xmlns:omgdi="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI" xmlns:design="http://flowable.org/design" typeLanguage="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" expressionLanguage="http://www.w3.org/1999/XPath" targetNamespace="http://ics.cat/cu3-lumbalgia" exporter="Flowable Design" exporterVersion="2025.2.04" design:palette="flowable-work-process-palette">
  <process id="Lumbalgia_Primaria_Anamnesis" name="Lumbalgia Primaria - Anamnesis" isExecutable="true">
    <documentation>POC Clinical Pathway Low Back Pain (v7).
Schema based on the client's "Lumbalgia Templates Simple" schema.

Triggers (3):
1st trigger · Reason for Encounter in the generic VISIT template → DMN1 decides process start.
2nd trigger · Red Flags in the Lumbalgia Checklist template.
3rd trigger · Yellow Flags in the Lumbalgia Checklist template.

DMNs:
· cu3_reason_for_encounter.dmn — input: diagnostic code; output: startProcess + processType.
· cu3_lumbalgia_flags_routing.dmn — input: redFlagsPresent + yellowFlagsPresent; output: triageDestination.

Planned openEHR templates (according to client schema):
· Generic VISIT template — Reason for Encounter, Anamnesis, Examination, Specific Questionnaire, PROM, Prescriptions, Requests.
· Lumbalgia Checklist Template — Red flags + Yellow flags.
· PROM Template — Self reported data EQ-5D-5L.
· Digital Asset Template — POS service request.
· Folder "POC Lumbalgia Templates" + ADMIN_COMPOSITION "POC care orchestration record" (Admin Folders).

Reference GPC: ICS Low Back Pain (https://scientiasalut.gencat.cat/handle/11351/4526.2).
Pending adjustment with the client: ICD/SNOMED codes in DMN1, set of Red/Yellow Flags and specific care pathway for Yellow Flags.</documentation>
